---
name: "Renderer import aliases"
description: "Use path aliases for renderer imports; keep imports stable and readable."
globs: ["app/renderer/src/**/*", "vite.config.mts", "tsconfig.json"]
alwaysApply: true
---

- Prefer aliases over deep relative imports in renderer code:
  - `@views/*` → `app/renderer/src/views/*`
  - `@features/*` → `app/renderer/src/ts/features/*`
  - `@ts/*` → `app/renderer/src/ts/*`
  - `@components/*` → `app/renderer/src/components/*`
  - `@renderer/*` → `app/renderer/src/*`
- If moving files, update imports to aliases rather than changing relative paths.
- Do not introduce new alias schemes; extend existing ones if truly needed.

